{
  "doc_id": "60156",
  "text": "A subdivision in two hierarchical levels has also been proposed for the cat spinal Central Pattern Generator (CPG) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] that controls locomotion. It was suggested that separate structures within the CPG would provide on the one hand the rhythm generation, on the other the pattern formation, i.e., shaping the final outflow to motoneurones according to the different tasks and contexts, under the influence of peripheral afferences (see also) [CITATION_3] .",
